I like how there are so many ways this can be interpreted, and conflicting resolutions to each one. The vague sentence ?) adds to the confusion.

There is a memetic hazard causing people to see pigs as people. Maybe created by an anomaly-possessing animal rights group? We should treat this as any other memetic hazard.
There is a reality-bending hazard that causes pigs to become conscious. We should contain the spread with high priority, and contain all the affected pigs and make sure their human rights are respected.
There is a memetic hazard that causes people to perceive others as pigs. Perhaps released by cannibals or meat manufacturers. It doesn't seem to be done that well, since the Foundation can tell they're still people in pig form. We should contain the memetic threat, and in the mean time spread propaganda to ensure pigs are treated humanely (wait.. is that why so many religions ban eating pork?)
There is a reality-bending hazard that causes people to turn into pigs, in body if not in mind. We should contain the spread with high priority, and contain all the affected pigs and make sure their human rights are respected.








